name: DAPUR DARINN

review 1: Indonesian culinary, with paddy field view. Nice place for early dinner or lunch. üëç
review 2: Ikan bakar was excellent with a good price for the paket deal.  Lovely view of the rice fields, clean, new, great koi pond and a nice breeze.  A good place for expats that want to try some local food.  Or run a meeting in the upstairs conference room.  The milkshake I think was just Milo and ice, ok, but not what I expected.  Thai iced tea didn't have much tea flavor.
